DR  PDBe; 3bfq;
CC  Forms the linear tip of the Type1 fimbria, a macromolecular cell
CC  surface structure required for cellular adhesion. The fimbria consists
CC  of a 1-2 um long fimbrial rod, built by thousands of copies of the
CC  non-adhesive major subunit, FimA (P04128). The tip is optimized to have
CC  a dual functionality: flexible exploration and force sensing. The 
CC  FimFGH subunits interact through donor strand complementation where a
CC  beta-strand from one subunit completes the beta-sandwich structure of
CC  the neighboring subunit. FimH contains a lectin domain which binds
CC  mannose derivatives on the surface of neighboring cells. 
